---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Uses"
  description="Tools, hardware, and software Chao Tan uses daily."
>
  <h1>Uses</h1>
  <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:2rem;">
    Tools I use daily. Inspired by <a href="https://uses.tech" rel="noopener">uses.tech</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Editor &amp; Terminal</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cursor</strong> — AI-native code editor (daily driver)</li>
      <li><strong>Claude Code</strong> — agentic coding in the terminal</li>
      <li><strong>zsh</strong> + oh-my-zsh</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Hardware</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>MacBook Pro (M-series)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Languages &amp; Frameworks</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Java — production workhorses at Amazon and Snowflake</li>
      <li>Python — ML pipelines, automation, data work</li>
      <li>TypeScript/Astro — this blog</li>
      <li>SQL — Snowflake daily</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>This blog</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Astro 6</strong> — static site framework</li>
      <li><strong>Tailwind CSS v4</strong> — styling</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> — hosting and CDN</li>
      <li><strong>Biome</strong> — linting and formatting</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Base>
